derived.tooltip: "HR Clock" is a High resolution clock recorded to the logfile by this pc when data arrives, resolution of 1 millisecond.
"MS-2 Clock" is the MegaSquirt clock returned by the ECU, this runs from 0-255 and recylcles indefinitely, resolution 1 second.
"PW" is the pulsewidth for injector channel 1. Resolution of 1 us.
"PW2" is the pulsewidth for injector channel 2. Resolution of 1 us.
"RPM" is the engine's speed in revolutions per minute.
"Spark Adv." is the Current spark advance being run.
"Squirt" is a bitfield containing information such as which injectors are firing, which are scheduled to fire, etc.

"EngineBits" is a bitfield containing information such as cranking/running, accel enrich, decel mode and warmup enrichment. It require decoding, use the information in unions.h for the "engine" union.
"WB02ena 1" is a flag indicating whether the wb afr reading is valid.
"WB02ena 2" is a flag indicating whether the wb afr reading is valid.
"Baro (kPa)" is the barometer reading in kPa.
"MAP (kPa)" is the manifold pressure reading in kPa.
"MAT (째)" is the manifold air temperature reading in degrees.
"CLT (째)" is the coolant temperature reading in degrees.
"TPS (%)" is the throttle position reading in percent of full scale.
"AFR 1" is the AFR from O2 sensor 1.
"AFR 2" is the AFR from O2 sensor 2.
"Knock" is the amount of spark retard due to knocking
"EGO Corr" is the AVERAGED EGO correction factor for both injectors/O2 sensors
"EGO Corr 1" is the EGO correction factor for injector1 and O2 sensor 1
"EGO Corr 2" is the EGO correction factor for injector2 and O2 sensor 2
"AIR Corr" is the AIR temp correction factor for both channels
"Warm Corr" is the current amount of warmup correction (%).
"Accel Enr." is the current amount of acceleration enrichment (ms).
"Fuel Cut" is the current amount of fuel cut (%).
"Barr Corr" is the current amount of Baro Correction (%).
"Gammae" is the sum of all enrichments.
"VE 1" is the current VE for injector channel 1.
"VE 2" is the current VE for injector channel 1.
"IAC Step" is the current position for the Stepper IAC (steps)
"IdleDC" is the current PWM idle dutycycle.
"Cold Adv (째)" is the current Cold spark advance addon.
"TPSdot" is the rate of change of the TPS signal.
"MAPdot" is the rate of change of the MAP signal.
"dwell" is a the amount of time the ignitin coil is energized in ms.
"Fuel Corr." is correction factor based on how mcuh alcohol is in the fuel.
"Port Status" is a bitfield showing the status of ports 0-6
"Knock Ret." is the current amount of spark retard due to knock.
"EAEFuelCorr1" is the current Ehnhanced Accel Enrich fuel correction for injector channel 1
"EGO Volts 1" is the current O2 sensor voltage for sensor 1
"EGO Volts 2" is the current O2 sensor voltage for sensor 2
"status1" is a status register for debug/info purposes
"status2" is a status register for debug/info purposes
"status3" is a status register for debug/info purposes
"status4" is a status register for debug/info purposes
"looptime" is the total time for the mainloop to process in uSec.
"tpsADC" is the raw TPS signal ADC value used for the calibrator.
"synccnt" is something to due with wheel decode...
"timing_err" is the accuracy of the timing predictor
"deltaT" is the normalized time between trigger pulses
"wallfuel1" is something for EAE in uSecs.
"EAEFuelCorr2" is EAE Fuel correction for inj channel 2 in uSec.
"boostduty" is pwm boost output duty cycle.
"vss1" is the output from vehicle speed sensor one in mph
"vss2" is the output from vehicle speed sensor one in mph
"Dcycle1" is the injector Duty cycle for injector channel 1.
"Dcycle2" is the injector Duty cycle for injector channel 2.
"AFR Error 1" is the difference between target AFR and actual AFR for the first O2 channel
"AFR Error 2" is the difference between target AFR and actual AFR for the second O2 channel.
"Lambda 1" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 1.
"Lambda 2" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 2.
"Lambda 3" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 3.
"Lambda 4" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 4.
"Lambda 5" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 5.
"Lambda 6" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 6.
"Lambda 7" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 7.
"Lambda 8" is the Lambda reading from O2 sensor 8.
"BoostBar" is the difference between the MAP and BARO inputs and scaled into BAR's
"BoostPSIg" is the difference between the MAP and BARO inputs and scaled to Gauge pressue
"Vacuum" is the difference between the BARO and MAP inputs and scaled into inches of Hg
